---
// Article 1.6: Reporting Scams (NSRC, CCID, Cyber999)
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../../components/Footer.astro';
import AudienceTabs from '../../../components/AudienceTabs.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../../components/panduan-rakyat/Breadcrumb';

const articleData = {
  sectionNumber: '01',
  sectionTitle: 'Safety and Emergencies',
  sectionIcon: '🚨',
  articleTitle: 'Reporting Scams (NSRC, CCID, Cyber999)',
  articleDescription: 'How to report online scams, fraud, and cybercrime',
  colorRgb: '220, 38, 38',
  lastUpdated: 'March 2026',
};

const simpleContent = `
  <h2 id="what-is-scam">What is a scam?</h2>
  <p>A scam is when someone tricks you to steal your money or personal information. Scammers often contact you by phone, message, or email pretending to be from banks, government offices, or companies you trust.</p>
  
  <h2 id="common-scams">Common scams in Malaysia:</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>📞 <strong>Phone scams:</strong> "Your bank account is compromised"</li>
    <li>💬 <strong>WhatsApp scams:</strong> "Hi, this is your old friend"</li>
    <li>📧 <strong>Email scams:</strong> "You won a prize! Click here"</li>
    <li>🛒 <strong>Online shopping scams:</strong> Fake online stores</li>
    <li>💰 <strong>Investment scams:</strong> "Get rich quick" schemes</li>
    <li>🎣 <strong>Phishing:</strong> Fake websites that look real</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="what-to-do">If you think you've been scammed:</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Stop all contact</strong> with the scammer immediately</li>
    <li><strong>Do NOT pay</strong> any more money</li>
    <li><strong>Report to NSRC:</strong> Call 15999 or visit nsrc.mcmc.gov.my</li>
    <li><strong>Report to police:</strong> Make a police report at your nearest station</li>
    <li><strong>Contact your bank:</strong> If you shared bank details</li>
  </ol>

  <h2 id="important-numbers">Important numbers:</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>NSRC Hotline:</strong> 15999 (24/7)</li>
    <li><strong>Police Emergency:</strong> 999</li>
    <li><strong>Cyber999 (MCMC):</strong> 1-800-888-999</li>
    <li><strong>Bank Negara:</strong> 1-300-88-5465</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="how-to-protect">How to protect yourself:</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Never share OTP, TAC, or passwords with anyone</li>
    <li>Check website URLs carefully (look for https://)</li>
    <li>Don't click on suspicious links</li>
    <li>Verify calls by calling the official number back</li>
    <li>Install scam blocker apps</li>
  </ul>
`;

const detailedContent = `
  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>Cybercrime and online scams have become increasingly sophisticated in Malaysia. The National Scam Response Centre (NSRC), Commercial Crime Investigation Department (CCID), and Cyber999 work together to combat online fraud and help victims recover losses.</p>

  <h2 id="types-of-scams">Common Types of Scams in Malaysia</h2>
  <table class="w-full border-collapse border border-border my-4">
    <thead>
      <tr class="bg-muted">
        <th class="border border-border p-3 text-left">Scam Type</th>
        <th class="border border-border p-3 text-left">How It Works</th>
        <th class="border border-border p-3 text-left">Red Flags</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-semibold">Macau Scam</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Caller claims to be from bank/police, says account compromised</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Urgency, requests for OTP/TAC, transfer to "safe account"</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-semibold">Love Scam</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Romantic relationship online, then asks for money</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Never meets in person, sob stories, investment opportunities</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-semibold">E-Commerce Scam</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Fake online store, products never delivered</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Prices too good, no physical address, new social media page</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-semibold">Investment Scam</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Promises high returns with low risk</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Guaranteed returns, pressure to invest quickly, unregistered company</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-semibold">Phishing</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Fake emails/websites stealing login details</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Suspicious URLs, spelling errors, urgent action required</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3 font-semibold">WhatsApp Scam</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">"Hi, this is your old friend" then asks for money</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Unknown number, vague messages, urgent money requests</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2 id="reporting-process">How to Report a Scam</h2>
  <h3>Step 1: Report to NSRC (National Scam Response Centre)</h3>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Call 15999</strong> (24/7 hotline) or visit <strong>nsrc.mcmc.gov.my</strong></li>
    <li>Provide details: scammer's phone number, bank account, social media profile</li>
    <li>NSRC will coordinate with banks to freeze scammer's accounts</li>
    <li>Get a reference number for your report</li>
  </ol>
  <p><strong>Time is critical:</strong> Report within 24 hours for best chance of recovering funds.</p>

  <h3>Step 2: Make a Police Report</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Visit your nearest police station</li>
    <li>Bring all evidence: screenshots, chat logs, transaction records</li>
    <li>Provide the NSRC reference number</li>
    <li>Get a copy of the police report for insurance/bank claims</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Step 3: Report to MCMC (for telecom/internet scams)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Visit <strong>aduan.skmm.gov.my</strong></li>
    <li>Or call <strong>1-800-888-999</strong> (Cyber999)</li>
    <li>Report scammer's phone number, website, or social media account</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Step 4: Contact Your Bank</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Call your bank's fraud hotline immediately</li>
    <li>Request to freeze your account if you shared details</li>
    <li>Change all passwords and PINs</li>
    <li>Monitor your statements for suspicious transactions</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="evidence-to-keep">Evidence to Keep</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>📱 Screenshots of all conversations</li>
    <li>📞 Call logs and phone numbers</li>
    <li>💳 Bank transfer receipts and statements</li>
    <li>📧 Email headers and content</li>
    <li>🔗 URLs of fake websites</li>
    <li>👤 Scammer's profile pictures and social media links</li>
    <li>📝 Any other relevant documentation</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="prevention">Prevention Tips</h2>
  <h3>Phone Scams:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Hang up immediately if caller asks for OTP/TAC</li>
    <li>Verify by calling the official number yourself</li>
    <li>Install scam blocker apps (Truecaller, Hiya)</li>
    <li>Register with DND (Do Not Disturb) list</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Online Shopping:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Check seller reviews and ratings</li>
    <li>Use escrow services (Shopee, Lazada buyer protection)</li>
    <li>Verify physical address and contact number</li>
    <li>Be wary of prices that are too good to be true</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Investment:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Check if company is registered with Securities Commission</li>
    <li>Verify with Bank Negara Malaysia</li>
    <li>Never invest based on social media ads alone</li>
    <li>Remember: high returns = high risk</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="important-numbers">Important Numbers & Resources</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>NSRC Hotline:</strong> 15999 (24/7)</li>
    <li><strong>NSRC Website:</strong> nsrc.mcmc.gov.my</li>
    <li><strong>Police Emergency:</strong> 999</li>
    <li><strong>CCID (Commercial Crime):</strong> 03-2031 9999</li>
    <li><strong>Cyber999 (MCMC):</strong> 1-800-888-999</li>
    <li><strong>MCMC Aduan:</strong> aduan.skmm.gov.my</li>
    <li><strong>Bank Negara:</strong> 1-300-88-5465 (BNMTELELINK)</li>
    <li><strong>SC Investor Alert List:</strong> sc.com.my (check unregistered companies)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="recovery">Can I Get My Money Back?</h2>
  <p>Recovery depends on how quickly you report:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Within 24 hours:</strong> High chance if funds haven't been withdrawn</li>
    <li><strong>24-72 hours:</strong> Moderate chance, depends on investigation</li>
    <li><strong>Beyond 72 hours:</strong> Lower chance, but still report for statistics and prevention</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Banks will investigate and may refund if you followed security protocols and reported promptly.</p>
`;

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "I transferred money to a scammer. Can I get it back?",
    answer: "Report to NSRC (15999) and your bank IMMEDIATELY. If reported within 24 hours and the funds haven't been withdrawn, there's a good chance of recovery. The bank will investigate and may refund if you followed security protocols."
  },
  {
    question: "The scammer has my IC number. What should I do?",
    answer: "Make a police report immediately. Monitor your credit report through CCRIS. Alert your bank to watch for suspicious activity. Consider filing a report with JPN if you suspect identity theft."
  },
  {
    question: "I received a suspicious call but didn't transfer money. Should I still report?",
    answer: "Yes! Report to NSRC (15999) or MCMC Aduan. This helps authorities track scam patterns and warn others. Block the number on your phone."
  },
  {
    question: "How do I check if an online store is legitimate?",
    answer: "Check for: physical address, phone number, customer reviews, social media presence, and secure payment methods. Search the store name + 'scam' online. Use platforms with buyer protection (Shopee, Lazada) instead of direct transfers."
  },
  {
    question: "Can I report scams anonymously?",
    answer: "Yes, MCMC Aduan allows anonymous reports. However, providing your contact details helps authorities follow up if they need more information. NSRC reports require your details for bank coordination."
  }
];

const headings = [
  { id: 'overview', title: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'types-of-scams', title: 'Common Types of Scams', level: 2 },
  { id: 'reporting-process', title: 'How to Report a Scam', level: 2 },
  { id: 'evidence-to-keep', title: 'Evidence to Keep', level: 2 },
  { id: 'prevention', title: 'Prevention Tips', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recovery', title: 'Can I Get My Money Back?', level: 2 },
];
---

<Layout title={`${articleData.articleTitle} | People's Guide | EduLaluan`}>
  <Header />

  <main class="min-h-screen bg-background">
    <!-- Article Header -->
    <section 
      class="relative overflow-hidden py-section-lg border-b"
      style={{
        '--section-color': `rgb(${articleData.colorRgb})`,
        'border-bottom-color': `rgb(${articleData.colorRgb})`
      }}
    >
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="max-w-4xl">
          <!-- Breadcrumb -->
          <Breadcrumb items={[
            { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
            { label: "People's Guide", href: '/panduan-rakyat' },
            { label: `Section ${articleData.sectionNumber}`, href: `/panduan-rakyat/section-${articleData.sectionNumber}` },
            { label: articleData.articleTitle }
          ]} />

          <!-- Back Button -->
          <a
            href={`/panduan-rakyat/section-${articleData.sectionNumber}`}
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-primary transition-colors mb-6"
          >
            <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7" />
            </svg>
            Back to Section {parseInt(articleData.sectionNumber).toString()}
          </a>

          <!-- Article Title -->
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mt-6">
            <div 
              class="flex h-16 w-16 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-xl text-3xl"
              style={{ 
                'backgroundColor': `rgb(${articleData.colorRgb})`,
                'color': 'white'
              }}
            >
              {articleData.sectionIcon}
            </div>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <p class="text-sm font-medium text-primary mb-1 tracking-wide uppercase">
                Section {parseInt(articleData.sectionNumber).toString()}: {articleData.sectionTitle}
              </p>
              <h1 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-foreground">
                {articleData.articleTitle}
              </h1>
              <p class="text-lg text-muted-foreground mt-3">
                {articleData.articleDescription}
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Article Content -->
    <section class="py-section-md bg-surface">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="flex gap-8 max-w-6xl mx-auto">
          <!-- Main Content -->
          <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
            <!-- Audience Tabs (Simple/Detailed) -->
            <AudienceTabs>
              <Fragment slot="simple" set:html={simpleContent} />
              <Fragment slot="detailed" set:html={detailedContent} />
            </AudienceTabs>

            <!-- FAQ Section -->
            <div class="mt-12">
              <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-6">
                Frequently Asked Questions
              </h2>
              <div class="space-y-3">
                {faqs.map((faq) => (
                  <details
                    class="group rounded-xl border bg-surface-elevated transition-all"
                  >
                    <summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between p-5 font-semibold text-foreground list-none">
                      {faq.question}
                      <svg
                        class="h-5 w-5 text-muted-foreground transition-transform group-open:rotate-180"
                        fill="none"
                        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                        stroke="currentColor"
                      >
                        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                      </svg>
                    </summary>
                    <div class="px-5 pb-5 text-muted-foreground">
                      {faq.answer}
                    </div>
                  </details>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Last Updated -->
            <div class="mt-12 pt-6 border-t border-border">
              <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
                <strong>Last updated:</strong> {articleData.lastUpdated}
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Table of Contents (Sidebar) -->
          <aside class="sticky top-24 hidden lg:block w-64 shrink-0">
            <nav class="space-y-1" aria-label="Table of contents">
              <h3 class="text-xs font-semibold text-muted-foreground uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">
                On This Page
              </h3>
              {headings.map((heading) => (
                <a
                  href={`#${heading.id}`}
                  class="block py-1.5 text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground transition-colors"
                  style={{ paddingLeft: `${(heading.level - 2) * 12 + 12}px` }}
                >
                  {heading.title}
                </a>
              ))}
            </nav>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Navigation Footer -->
    <section class="py-section-md bg-background">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
          <div class="rounded-2xl border bg-surface-elevated p-6">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 text-muted-foreground">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
              </svg>
              <p class="text-sm">
                <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide provides general information only. Always verify with official sources for the most current information.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Section padding utilities */
  :root {
    --section-padding-lg: clamp(3rem, 5vw + 1rem, 5rem);
    --section-padding-md: clamp(2rem, 3vw + 1rem, 3rem);
  }

  .py-section-lg {
    padding-top: var(--section-padding-lg);
    padding-bottom: var(--section-padding-lg);
  }

  .py-section-md {
    padding-top: var(--section-padding-md);
    padding-bottom: var(--section-padding-md);
  }

  /* Article Typography */
  .prose-panduan {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--foreground);
  }

  .prose-panduan h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--foreground);
  }

  .prose-panduan h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--foreground);
  }

  .prose-panduan p {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .prose-panduan ul,
  .prose-panduan ol {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .prose-panduan li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .prose-panduan a {
    color: var(--primary);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .prose-panduan a:hover {
    color: var(--primary-dark);
  }

  .prose-panduan strong {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--foreground);
  }

  .prose-panduan table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .prose-panduan th {
    background-color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 0.75rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .prose-panduan td {
    padding: 0.75rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .prose-panduan .bg-muted {
    background-color: var(--muted);
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }
</style>
